DefaultEvent.Description:
Days of back-breaking labour unearth a cache of old bones, curios... and a meteorite. A broken armature of steel and copper sheathes its sides. The zailors fall back before it as the glyphs on its side crawl with fire.

"This is it!!" the Cannoneer cries. "This must be what broke the roof. (It's very frightening.) A Seal of the Red Science!! I never thought I'd see such a thing. But it's sleeping. We'll need a Judgements' Egg, and my friends in the Iron Republic. We might be able to find an Egg in Irem." (The crew shrink back a little.) "Oh, such larks. Such larks!!"

[Take the Seal, and a Judgements' Egg, to the Iron Republic, south of London.]
DefaultEvent.Teaser: Days of back-breaking labour unearth a cache of old bones, curios...
DefaultEvent.Name: Aestival's Secret

ChildBranches.Name: Seek the Iron & Misery company prototype component
ChildBranches.Description: The Cannoneer points. "There. The black rocks on the south side of the island, where nothing grows. We'll need labour and supplies to dig it out." [This will consume the Supplies, but not the Crew.]

DefaultEvent.Description:
A garden overgrown with berry-bushes. A wooden trestle-table, set for a meal. Chairs strewn with bones - a half-dozen skeletons. A red-breasted bird perches on a grinning cranium. It cocks an eye at you, and bursts into song: a liquid, thrilling sound. It seems unperturbed as you approach to poke through the bones.

No signs of violence. No fire, no bullets, no bites. These people died peacefully, sitting down to breakfast, as the Surface sunlight spilled over them. Sunlight can kill at any time. The longer you remain here, the more danger you're in. So why did they stay?

Perhaps they stayed because Aestival is as beautiful as anywhere in the Neath, and ten times as generous. It's a fine place for a colony. You could found your own pocket kingdom... if you could do something about the sun. But what? What has power over sunlight? What makes the impossible, possible?
DefaultEvent.Name: Red bird singing

ChildBranches.Name: Investigate the ruins
ChildBranches.Description: There was some sort of installation here - and what looks like a handsome country house. Who was here? And what happened to them?

DefaultEvent.Description: The box will remain filled with light until it's opened, even underground. They do it with mirrors.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: The box will remain filled with light until it's opened, even underground...
DefaultEvent.Name: Snap it shut

RareDefaultEvent.Description: You fill the box successfully... but the sunlight has lit a fire in your bones. You struggle back to the ship and wait while the fever subsides. Be wary. This is true sunlight, and it can be unpredictable death to those who've spent too long here below.
RareDefaultEvent.Name: Mortal measures

ChildBranches.Name: Fill a Mirrorcatch Box
ChildBranches.Description: Is this really sunlight? Then open the Box wide. Let it brim. [Warning: this may increase your Wounds.]

DefaultEvent.Description: Breadfruit, sugar-cane, coconut. Soft-shelled crabs and plump birds too stupid to know a hungry zailor from a tree. Aestival is ripe with treasures unknown in the Neath. Fill your hold.
DefaultEvent.Name: Exotic delights

RareDefaultEvent.Description: You fill your stores with breadfruit, sugar-cane, coconut. Soft-shelled crabs and plump birds too stupid to know a hungry zailor from a tree. But on the way back to the ship, one of your crew topples over with a groan. She's smiling blissfully. "Go on, cap'n," she says. "I've missed the zun." Her eyes close. Sunlight is perilous for those who've lived in the Neath too long.
RareDefaultEvent.Teaser: You fill your stores with breadfruit, sugar-cane, coconut...
RareDefaultEvent.Name: Exotic delights

ChildBranches.Name: Gather supplies
ChildBranches.Description: The jungle here bursts with life.

DefaultEvent.Description: Zailors heave and shout, raise cranes and lift blocks. They're nervous to begin with, but as the day wears on and no one falls to the sunlight, their spirits rise. So, too, do the walls of your new dwelling...
DefaultEvent.Teaser: Zailors heave and shout, raise cranes and lift blocks...
DefaultEvent.Name: The work begins

ChildBranches.Name: Prepare to found a colony
ChildBranches.Description: Begin to rebuild this place; and set Dawn's Law as the cornerstone, to shield you from the dangers of the sunlight.

ChildBranches.Name: Go beachcombing
ChildBranches.Description: If you're lucky, you might pick up treasures. More likely, you'll pick up bits of wood, and the occasional interesting arthropod.

DefaultEvent.Description: It bounces swiftly across the sun-hot sand, using a minimum of tendrils on the scorching beach. Somewhat shrivelled, it snuggles into the shade of a fruit-rich tree. It seems unwilling to go further.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: It bounces swiftly across the sun-hot sand, using a minimum of tendrils on the scorching beach...
DefaultEvent.Name: A nimble scuttle

ChildBranches.Name: Put a blemmigan ashore
ChildBranches.Description: Fallen fruit enriches the soil. Perhaps this will give the timid mushroom strength to resist the sun's rays.

DefaultEvent.Description: Your eyes water, the pages blur. The report is one of joy-filled complaint - Aestival has a beauty too bright to be appreciated. But perhaps the Admiralty can find something of use.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: Your eyes water, the pages blur...
DefaultEvent.Name: A burning afterimage.

ChildBranches.Name: Visit your colony
ChildBranches.Description: You've begun something extraordinary. Let's see how it's going.

ChildBranches.Name: Prepare to found a colony
ChildBranches.Description: Begin to rebuild this place; and set the Parabox at its heart, to shield you from the dangers of the sunlight.

DefaultEvent.Description: You've changed the nature of sunlight here. It's still warm. It still glows on the skin. But the box won't fill.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: You've changed the nature of sunlight here...
DefaultEvent.Name: A faded glory

DefaultEvent.Description: The Jewel of the Zee. The only true light in the darkness of the Neath. Years ago, your predecessor conquered the power of sunlight and established a blossoming colony. Now, it's a sovereign nation in its own right, albeit a small one. Zailors flock to the single ray of sunlight in the Neath. Aestival has become a beacon of safety in the near-east of the Zee. There are even those who journey east from here, following the song of Salt. Aestival has grown, but there is always room for improvement...
DefaultEvent.Teaser: The Jewel of the Zee. The only true light in the darkness of the Neath. Years ago, your predecessor conquered the power of sunlight and established a blossoming colony. Now, it's a sovereign nation in its own right. Zailors flock to the single ray of sunlight in the Neath. Aestival has become a beacon of safety in the near-east of the Zee. There are even those who journey east from here, following the song of Salt. Aestival has become strong, but there is always room for improvement...

ChildBranches.Name: Visit the Nation
ChildBranches.Description: A tiny Kingdom flourishes on the island.

Description:
Sun! A great beam of sunlight bathes the island! Squint into the dazzle: far above, there's a hole in the roof.

In that light you see beaches of white-gold sand; trees heavy with bright fruit; the reds and blues and greens of the Surface.
Name: Aestival

ChildBranches.Name: Examine the artefact shielding the Kingdom from the searing effects of sunlight

DefaultEvent.Description: This land is yours; this ship is yours.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: This land is yours; this ship is yours...
DefaultEvent.Name: A satisfactory result

ChildBranches.Name: Repair your ship
ChildBranches.Description: This little drydock isn't exactly the Admiralty Shipyards; but you can manage repairs that would be impossible at zee. [This will completely repair your Hull at the cost of 150 echoes.]

DefaultEvent.Description: Fresh Supplies. Well, as fresh as supplies can be expected to be on the Zee.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: Fresh Supplies. Well, as fresh as supplies can be expected to be on the Zee...
DefaultEvent.Name: Resupplied

ChildBranches.Name: Resupply your ship
ChildBranches.Description: Purchase supplies for your ship. [This will supply you with 1 supply for the cost of 25 echoes]

DefaultEvent.Teaser: Fresh Supplies. Well, as fresh as supplies can be expected to be on the Zee...
DefaultEvent.Name: Resupplied

ChildBranches.Name: Refuel your ship
ChildBranches.Description: Tap into the Kingdom's fuel reserves to refuel your ship. [This will supply you with 1 fuel for 15 echoes]

DefaultEvent.Description: Sunlight is enough to bring the most jaded of zailors to tears. The sunlight of Aestival is made all the more sweeter by the fact that it isn't killing them.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: Sunlight is enough to bring the most jaded of zailors to tears. The sunlight of Aestival is made all the more sweeter by the fact that it isn't killing them.
DefaultEvent.Name: A welcome respite

ChildBranches.Name: Shore leave!
ChildBranches.Description: Eat, drink, and bathe in the sweet sunlight. [Aestival will reduce terror in exchange for supplies]

Description: The Kingdom of Sunlight, loyal (mostly) to you. [WIP]
Name: The Kingdom of Sunlight

DefaultEvent.Description: There is nothing for you here. You return to civilization.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: There is nothing for you here. You return to civilization.
DefaultEvent.Name: An otherworldly power

ChildBranches.Name: Return to the Kingdom
ChildBranches.Description: There is nothing for you here. You return to civilization.

DefaultEvent.Description:
You approach the tiny artefact that made this entire kingdom possible. To your surprise, a pinprick of glowing light rises from the artefact and speaks to you.

"Greetings, Captain! It is I, Psifrost/FrostyFridge, the creator of this mod. As you can see, Aestival has changed a bit. Currently, the mod is pretty bare-bones, you are only able to buy supplies, fuel, and repairs with echoes. There's a lot planned beyond this though. Here's a short list of what's planned:

Upgrades for the Kingdom: In the future, you'll be able to upgrade Aestival even further.

Relations with other powers: Your Kingdom will change depending on who you ally with.

General bugfixing and polishing: As you can probably tell, I made this mod in a few hours, so not everything is in the place I want it to be.

Be sure to check back here after you download a new version. Leave any suggestions, bug reports, criticisms, and hate-mail on the mod's page on Steam. Enjoy!"
DefaultEvent.Name: An otherworldly power
